body:
- Adds caching everything on demand through Preferences
- Removes duplicate videos.

NOTE: The manifest loaded from Apple includes some video files twice, although with different names. Aerial now goes through and does a HEAD request to all videos to get their content lengths and culls the list with that added information. Takes a second longer to start the screensaver, so I'll be looking into caching this in the future.

name: 1.2 Beta 4
body:
Offline Mode added
Fixes bug where cache setting wasn't shown correctly in preferences window.

name: 1.2 Beta 3
body:
Fixes black screen issue.
Fixes hot corner issue.

name: 1.2 Beta 2
body: Fixes issue with last beta where next video wouldn't play

name: 1.2 Beta
body:
1.2 Beta adds automatic caching as videos play

![screen shot 2015-10-29 at 8 21 35 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/967800/10837778/aa5c0e1a-7e7a-11e5-9918-4032304e3212.png)

Previous version required Yosemite, 1.1 is now Mavericks compatible, but will show videos in aspect ratio mode instead of fill mode.

Added custom thumbnail.
Now gives an error if trying to install on an unsupported OS X version.
Removed debug log.  (Thanks to @nheagy, Issue https://github.com/JohnCoates/Aerial/issues/1)
